    "The only difference is that the kernels are specialized for these alternate regularizers; specifically the kernels are based on the decomposable regularization function's sub-differential (Negahban et al., 2012).",
    "All preceding influence methods-static, gradient-based and retraining-based-define and estimate influence using only final model parameters, (T) D, where D ⊆ D.",
